kanji.koohii1: Sun and blue sky! Yep/ the weather´s cleared up!

short_text_with_quiz.text_japanese:
昨晩、作曲にかかっていました。想像以上に困難で、メロディーがなかなか決まらず、いつまでも終わらない作業の最中でした。結果、まだ苦労していますが、続ける覚悟をしました。この作曲を完成させることを希望します。

これからも頑張りたいと思います。望みを諦めません。困難も覚悟します。有能な作曲家になりたいと望みます。これが私の最終的な希望です。
short_text_with_quiz.text_english:
Last night, I was working on a musical composition.  It was more difficult than I expected.  The melody wouldn't flow, and I felt the process was never-ending.  As a result, I'm still struggling, but I've made the decision to continue. I hope to complete this composition. 

I hope to continue working hard. I will not give up on my wish. I am prepared for the difficulties. I want to be a capable composer.  This is my final hope.

song_lyrics.lyrics_english_translation:
Last night, I dreamt of the best jeans, a final wish.
Hoping for a capable tailor, I spent last year learning the craft.
I'm in the middle of making them now, a difficult task. 
But as a result of my hard work, most of the seams are done.
The syrupy consistency of the glue is the worst part! 
Tuesday, I have an applicant coming. 
I hope for a successful result, I desire it with all my heart. 
I'm ready. I'm not giving up. It will be finished; I have hope.
The consumption is high, but I want it to last forever.
This composition is half-finished, but it will be the best.
